    • 方法详细资料

      • addSpy

        public java.lang.String addSpy(java.lang.String name,
                               java.lang.String title,
                               java.lang.String location,
                               java.lang.String password)
        Web service operation Pre: A name, title, location, and password are provided as input. Post: A new spy is added to the list of spies. The value returned is a simple String representation of the spy.

      • updateSpy

        public java.lang.String updateSpy(java.lang.String name,
                                  java.lang.String title,
                                  java.lang.String location,
                                  java.lang.String password)
        Web service operation Pre: A name, title, location, and password are provided as input. Post: An existing spy is updated. The value returned is a simple String representation of the updated spy.

      • getSpy

        public java.lang.String getSpy(java.lang.String name)
        Web service operation Pre: A name is provided as input. Post: An existing spy is returned as a string. If no such spy exists then the message “No such spy” is returned.

      • deleteSpy

        public java.lang.String deleteSpy(java.lang.String name)
        Web service operation Pre: A spy name is provided as input. Post: The spy is deleted from the list of spies. The value returned is a simple String that says “Spy” “was deleted from the list.”

      • getList

        public java.lang.String getList()
        Web service operation Pre: None Post: A simple string is returned that contains all of the spy data on the spy list. If the list is empty then an empty string is returned.

      • getListAsXML

        public java.lang.String getListAsXML()
        Web service operation Pre: None Post: An XML simple string is returned that contains all of the spy data on the list. If the list is empty then an empty XML string is returned. The XML string has a start and an end tag but no spies.
